findings.hepatobiliary: Multiple hypodense liver lesions, largest 1.2 cm, characterized as hemangiomas.
findings.spleen: Normal size and attenuation, no focal lesions.
findings.urinary: 2 subcentimeter hypodensities in lower pole of left kidney, unchanged, characterized as angiomyolipomas.
findings.gastrointestinal: Multiple diverticular in descending and sigmoid colon, focal segment of sigmoid colonic wall thickening, microperforation indicated by extra-luminal air and free fluid.
findings.pelvis: No abnormalities, urinary bladder and distal ureters are unremarkable.

laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: The hypodensities in the kidneys and liver lesions have been previously characterized and are unchanged.
